The paper deals with image inpainting using deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method is based on the generative adversarial network (GAN) framework, which is a popular approach in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves training the network to capture both local and global features in images, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves image processing and manipulation, which is a topic in computer graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
